(505, NULL, 30, 2, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', '[Specific Learning Outcome — Lesson 7]', 'Lesson 7 — 4.1 Bar Graphs\n\nBy the end of this lesson, learners should be able to:\na) [Fill in Specific Learning Outcome (a)]\nb) [Fill in Specific Learning Outcome (b)]', '[Core learning experience — Lesson 7]', '• [Describe Learning Experience activity for lesson 7]\n• [Share findings with class]', 'How do we compare information using bar graphs?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 16:52:32', '2026-04-10 16:52:32', NULL),
(506, NULL, 30, 3, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', '[Specific Learning Outcome — Lesson 8]', 'Lesson 8 — 4.1 Bar Graphs\n\nBy the end of this lesson, learners should be able to:\na) [Fill in Specific Learning Outcome (a)]\nb) [Fill in Specific Learning Outcome (b)]', '[Core learning experience — Lesson 8]', '• [Describe Learning Experience activity for lesson 8]\n• [Share findings with class]', 'How do we answer questions from a bar graph?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 16:52:32', '2026-04-10 16:52:32', NULL),
(507, NULL, 30, 4, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', '[Specific Learning Outcome — Lesson 9]', 'Lesson 9 — 4.1 Bar Graphs\n\nBy the end of this lesson, learners should be able to:\na) [Fill in Specific Learning Outcome (a)]\nb) [Fill in Specific Learning Outcome (b)]', '[Core learning experience — Lesson 9]', '• [Describe Learning Experience activity for lesson 9]\n• [Share findings with class]', 'How do we draw and interpret horizontal bar graphs?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 16:52:32', '2026-04-10 16:52:32', NULL),
(508, NULL, 30, 5, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', '[Specific Learning Outcome — Lesson 10]', 'Lesson 10 — 4.1 Bar Graphs\n\nBy the end of this lesson, learners should be able to:\na) [Fill in Specific Learning Outcome (a)]\nb) [Fill in Specific Learning Outcome (b)]', '[Core learning experience — Lesson 10]', '• [Describe Learning Experience activity for lesson 10]\n• [Share findings with class]', 'How do I demonstrate understanding of bar graphs?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 16:52:32', '2026-04-10 16:52:32', NULL),
(509, 3, 1, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'use place value and total value of digits up to millions in real life', 'a) Identify the place value of digits up to millions in a given number.\r\nb) State the position of any digit in a seven-digit number.', 'use place value and total value of digits up to millions in real life', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of place value by responding to guiding questions and completing steps using the chalkboard or tablet.\r\n* Perform or solve place value exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\r\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use place value to identify and describe the position of digits in a seven-digit number?', 'Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Locally available number charts or homemade charts using cardboard and sticks\n* Container filled with soil or sand to demonstrate place value using natural materials', 'Oral questions\n* Written exercise in exercise books to assess understanding of place value and digit positions', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-12 09:51:02', NULL),
(510, 3, 1, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'use place value and total value of digits up to millions', 'a) Determine the total value of digits in numbers up to millions.\r\nb) Calculate the value of specific digits within a seven-digit figure.', 'use place value and total value of digits up to millions', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of total value by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\r\n* Perform or solve total value exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\r\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find the total value of each digit in the number 4,832,157?', '* Learners textbook\n* Number cards (0-9) made from manila paper\n* Small stones, seeds, or bottle tops for counting/grouping\n* Place value chart drawn on manila paper or chalkboard\n* Slips of paper for writing numbers up to millions', '* Written exercise: Solve problems calculating the value of specific digits in given seven-digit numbers.\n* Observation: Monitor learners as they work in groups using number cards and place value charts to demonstrate understanding.', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-12 09:51:09', NULL),
(511, 3, 1, 3, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'read and write numbers up to 100,000 in words in real life', 'a) Read numbers up to 100,000 in words correctly.\nb) Write given figures up to 100,000 in word form with correct spelling.', 'read and write numbers up to 100,000 in words in real life', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of reading and writing numbers by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve writing exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we accurately read and write the number 87,452 in words?', '* Learners textbook\n* Number cards (0-9) made from manila paper\n* Place value chart drawn on manila paper or chalkboard\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Sticks and small stones for grouping tens and hundreds', '* Written exercise: Individual work converting given figures up to 100,000 into word form.\n* Oral questions: Quick-fire questioning on reading numbers displayed on number cards or the chalkboard.', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-12 09:51:15', NULL),
(512, 3, 1, 4, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'order numbers up to 100,000 in real-life situations', 'a) Compare numbers up to 100,000 using symbols (<, >).\nb) Arrange a set of numbers up to 100,000 in ascending order.', 'order numbers up to 100,000 in real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of ascending order by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve ordering exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use comparison symbols and ordering to show which numbers are greater or smaller when working with numbers up to 100,000?', '* Learners textbook\n* Number cards (0-9) made from cardboard or paper\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing symbols <, >, = with examples', '* Oral questions during comparison and ordering demonstrations\n* Written exercise comparing and arranging numbers up to 100,000\n* Observation during group ordering activities', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(513, 3, 1, 5, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'order numbers up to 100,000 in real-life situation', 'a) Arrange a set of numbers up to 100,000 in descending order.\r\nb) Identify the largest and smallest numbers in a provided set.', 'order numbers up to 100,000 in real-life situation', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of descending order by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\r\n* Perform or solve ordering exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\r\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we arrange numbers from greatest to smallest and identify which number is the largest or smallest in a set?', '* Learners textbook\n* Number cards (0-9 digits written on cardboard pieces)\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of descending order concepts\n* Written exercise where learners arrange given sets of numbers up to 100,000 in descending order and identify largest and smallest numbers', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(514, 3, 2, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'round off numbers up to 100,000 to the nearest thousand', 'a) Identify the thousands digit and the rounding digit (hundreds).\nb) Round off whole numbers up to 100,000 to the nearest thousands.', 'round off numbers up to 100,000 to the nearest thousand', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of rounding to the nearest thousand by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve rounding exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we round off whole numbers up to 100,000 to the nearest thousand?', '* Learners textbook\n* Number charts showing place values up to hundred thousands\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Sticks or stones (for demonstrating grouping in thousands)', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of identifying thousands and hundreds digits\n* Written exercise where learners individually round off given numbers to the nearest thousand', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(515, 3, 2, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'round off numbers up to 100,000', 'a) Identify the tens of thousand digit.\nb) Round off whole numbers up to 100,000 to the nearest tens of thousand.', 'round off numbers up to 100,000', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of rounding to the tens of thousands by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve rounding exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we round whole numbers to the nearest tens of thousands to make estimation easier in everyday situations?', '* Learners textbook\n* Number charts showing place value up to hundred thousands\n* Number cards (10,000 to 100,000)\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Manila paper or cardboard for making place value charts', '* Oral questions during interactive demonstration to check understanding of tens of thousands digit identification\n* Written exercise with rounding problems to assess individual ability to round numbers to nearest tens of thousands', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(516, 3, 2, 3, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'apply squares of whole numbers up to 100', 'a) Multiply a whole number by itself to find its square.\nb) Calculate the squares of whole numbers up to 100 accurately.', 'apply squares of whole numbers up to 100', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of squares by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve square exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find the result when a whole number is multiplied by itself?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Multiplication tables chart\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Squared paper or ruled exercise books for organizing calculations', '* Written exercise: Learners calculate squares of given whole numbers up to 100 and show their working.\n* Oral questions: Ask learners to explain the process of squaring a number and give examples.', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(517, 3, 2, 4, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'apply square roots of perfect squares up to 10,000', 'a) Identify the square root of perfect squares up to 10,000.\nb) Use the factor tree or inverse method to find square roots.', 'apply square roots of perfect squares up to 10,000', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of square roots by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve square root exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find the original number when we know its square?', '* Learners textbook\n* Multiplication tables chart\n* Number cards (1-100)\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books', '* Written exercise solving square roots of perfect squares up to 10,000 using factor tree and inverse methods\n* Oral questions asking learners to explain the steps used to find square roots', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(518, 3, 2, 5, '1.0 Numbers', '1.1 Whole Numbers', 'appreciate use of whole numbers in real-life situations', 'a) Solve real-life problems involving whole numbers (place value, rounding, and squares).\nb) Evaluate personal progress through a summary exercise.', 'appreciate use of whole numbers in real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive review of whole numbers by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve a summary assessment exercise individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use our understanding of place value, rounding, and squares to solve problems we encounter in our daily lives?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chart paper or chalkboard for reviewing key concepts\n* Locally available items for real-life problem scenarios (stones for counting, sticks for grouping)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Written exercise (summary assessment on whole numbers problems)\n* Self-assessment (learners evaluate their own progress and identify areas needing improvement)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(519, 3, 3, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.2 Multiplication', 'multiply up to a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number in real-life situations', 'a) Multiply a 4-digit number by a 1-digit number accurately.', 'multiply up to a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number in real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of multiplication by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve multiplication exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we multiply a 4-digit number by a 1-digit number?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(520, 3, 3, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.2 Multiplication', 'multiply up to a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number', 'By the end of the lesson, the learner should be able to:\na) Multiply a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number using long multiplication.', 'multiply up to a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number', 'Learner is guided to:\n* Engage in an interactive demonstration of multiplication by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\r\n* Perform or solve multiplication exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\r\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use the long multiplication method to multiply a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number?', '* Learners textbook\r\n* Chalkboard and chalk\r\n* Exercise books and pencils\r\n* Place value cards made from cardboard', '* Written exercise: Learners solve 4-digit by 2-digit multiplication problems using long multiplication method\r\n* Observation: Monitor learners\' step-by-step working during guided practice to identify errors in place value alignment and carrying', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(521, 3, 3, 3, '1.0 Numbers', '1.2 Multiplication', 'estimate products by rounding off numbers being multiplied to the nearest ten', 'a) Estimate products using the compatibility of numbers.', 'estimate products by rounding off numbers being multiplied to the nearest ten', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of multiplication by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve multiplication exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use compatible numbers to estimate the product before multiplying?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Number cards (0-9) made from cardboard or paper\n* Chart showing multiplication tables', '* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of estimation strategies\n* Written exercise with problems requiring learners to estimate products before calculating actual answers', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(522, 3, 3, 4, '1.0 Numbers', '1.2 Multiplication', 'make patterns involving multiplication of numbers not exceeding 1,000', 'a) Create patterns involving multiplication of numbers not exceeding 1,000.', 'make patterns involving multiplication of numbers not exceeding 1,000', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of multiplication patterns by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve pattern exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we create and extend patterns using multiplication of numbers up to 1,000?', '* Learners textbook\n* Multiplication tables chart\n* Number cards (1-100) made from cardboard or paper\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Chalkboard and chalk', '* Oral questions during interactive demonstration to check understanding of pattern rules\n* Written exercise where learners create and complete their own multiplication patterns\n* Observation of group work to assess ability to identify and extend patterns', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(523, 3, 3, 5, '1.0 Numbers', '1.3 Division', 'divide up to a 4-digit number by up to a 3-digit number where the dividend is greater than the divisor', 'a) Identify the steps of dividing a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number.\nb) Divide a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number without a remainder.', 'divide up to a 4-digit number by up to a 3-digit number where the dividend is greater than the divisor', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of division by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve division exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we break down dividing a large number into simple, manageable steps?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Multiplication tables chart\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Written exercise (learners solve division problems with 4-digit numbers divided by 2-digit numbers)\n* Oral questions (learners explain the steps of division during the lesson)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(524, 3, 4, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.3 Division', 'divide up to a 4-digit number by up to a 3-digit number', 'a) Divide a 4-digit number by a 2-digit number with a remainder.\nb) State the quotient and the remainder correctly.', 'divide up to a 4-digit number by up to a 3-digit number', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of division by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve division exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find out how many groups of a 2-digit number fit into a 4-digit number, and what is left over?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Multiplication tables chart\n* Bundles of sticks (groups of 10s and 100s) for place value demonstration\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Written exercise: Learners solve 5-8 division problems involving 4-digit numbers divided by 2-digit numbers, clearly showing quotient and remainder\n* Oral questions: Asking individual learners to explain their division steps and identify the quotient and remainder from sample problems', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(525, 3, 4, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.3 Division', 'divide up to a 4-digit number by up to a 3-digit number', 'a) Divide a 4-digit number by a 3-digit number without a remainder.\nb) Work out the steps of long division for 3-digit divisors accurately.', 'divide up to a 4-digit number by up to a 3-digit number', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of division by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve division exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use long division to solve problems involving sharing or grouping large quantities by hundreds?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Place value counters or stones (representing thousands, hundreds, tens, ones)\n* Multiplication tables chart', '* Written exercise: Learners solve 4-digit by 3-digit division problems showing all steps of long division\n* Observation: Teacher monitors learners\' accuracy in following the long division procedure during individual or group work', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(526, 3, 4, 3, '1.0 Numbers', '1.3 Division', 'divide up to a 4-digit number by up to a 3-digit number', 'a) Divide a 4-digit number by a 3-digit number with a remainder.\nb) Interpret remainders in real-life division scenarios.', 'divide up to a 4-digit number by up to a 3-digit number', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of division by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve division exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we interpret and use remainders when dividing larger numbers in everyday situations like sharing items or distributing resources?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Counters (beans, stones, or bottle caps)\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Multiplication table chart', '* Written exercise solving 4-digit by 3-digit division problems with interpretation of remainders\n* Oral questions asking learners to explain what remainders mean in real-life contexts', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(527, 3, 4, 4, '1.0 Numbers', '1.3 Division', 'estimate quotients by rounding off the dividend and divisor', 'a) Round off the dividend and divisor to the nearest ten.\nb) Estimate quotients by dividing the rounded numbers.', 'estimate quotients by rounding off the dividend and divisor', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of division by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve division exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can rounding numbers help us estimate division answers quickly in everyday situations?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Number charts showing multiples of 10\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of rounding\n* Written exercise with problems requiring learners to round dividends and divisors, then estimate quotients', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(528, 3, 4, 5, '1.0 Numbers', '1.3 Division', 'perform combined operations up to 3-digit number', 'a) Identify the order of combined operations (BODMAS/PEMDAS).\nb) Perform combined operations involving addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.', 'perform combined operations up to 3-digit number', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of division by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve division exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we decide which operation to perform first when solving a problem with addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division all together?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing BODMAS/PEMDAS order\n* Locally made flashcards with different operations symbols (+, −, ×, ÷, brackets)', '* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of the order of operations\n* Written exercise with problems involving combined operations to assess individual application of BODMAS/PEMDAS', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(529, 3, 5, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.4 Fractions', 'add fractions using LCM in different situations', 'a) Define the term Least Common Multiple (LCM).\nb) Identify the LCM of denominators in given sets of fractions.', 'add fractions using LCM in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of finding LCM by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve LCM exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we find the LCM of denominators in given fractions?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(530, 3, 5, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.4 Fractions', 'add fractions using LCM', 'a) Use the LCM to add proper fractions with different denominators.\nb) Work out addition problems involving more than two fractions.', 'add fractions using LCM', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of adding fractions by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve addition exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we add fractions with different denominators using the LCM?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Rectangular and circular paper cut-outs (from old exercise books or newspapers)\n* Counters (stones, seeds, or bottle caps)', '* Oral questions during the demonstration to check understanding of LCM and fraction addition steps\n* Written exercise with problems on adding proper fractions with different denominators individually', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(531, 3, 5, 3, '1.0 Numbers', '1.4 Fractions', 'subtract fractions using LCM in different situations', 'a) Use the LCM to subtract proper fractions with different denominators.\nb) Solve subtraction problems involving fractions in real-life contexts.', 'subtract fractions using LCM in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of subtracting fractions by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve subtraction exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use the Least Common Multiple to subtract fractions with different denominators in everyday situations?', '* Learners textbook\n* Circular and rectangular cut-outs (paper or cardboard)\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Counters (bottle tops, stones, or seeds)', '* Written exercise (solving subtraction problems involving fractions with different denominators)\n* Oral questions (explaining steps of using LCM to subtract fractions)\n* Observation (monitoring learners\' work during group activities)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(532, 3, 5, 4, '1.0 Numbers', '1.4 Fractions', 'add mixed numbers in different situations', 'a) Convert mixed numbers into improper fractions for addition.\nb) Add mixed numbers by grouping whole numbers and fractions separately.', 'add mixed numbers in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of adding mixed numbers by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve addition exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we add mixed numbers by converting them to improper fractions or by grouping whole numbers and fractions separately?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Rectangular paper cut-outs or cardboard pieces\n* Locally available counters (stones, seeds, or bottle caps)', '* Written exercise solving addition of mixed numbers using both methods\n* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of conversion and grouping steps', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(533, 3, 5, 5, '1.0 Numbers', '1.4 Fractions', 'subtract mixed numbers in different situations', 'a) Convert mixed numbers into improper fractions for subtraction.\nb) Subtract mixed numbers accurately using the regrouping/borrowing method.', 'subtract mixed numbers in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of subtracting mixed numbers by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve subtraction exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we subtract mixed numbers when the fraction part of the first number is smaller than the fraction part of the second number?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Circular or rectangular paper cut-outs (for demonstrating fraction parts)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of conversion and regrouping steps\n* Written exercise with subtraction problems requiring learners to convert and subtract mixed numbers using the borrowing method', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(534, 3, 6, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.4 Fractions', 'identify reciprocal of proper fractions up to a 2-digit number', 'a) Define the term \"reciprocal\" of a fraction.\nb) Identify and write the reciprocals of proper fractions up to a 2-digit number.', 'identify reciprocal of proper fractions up to a 2-digit number', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of reciprocals by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve reciprocal exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find the reciprocal of a proper fraction and use it to solve problems?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Rectangular paper cut-outs or cardboard pieces\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during interactive demonstration to check understanding of reciprocals\n* Written exercise where learners identify and write reciprocals of given proper fractions\n* Observation during group work to assess ability to apply procedures', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(535, 3, 6, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.4 Fractions', 'work out squares of fractions', 'a) Multiply a fraction by itself to find its square.\nb) Calculate squares of fractions with a 1-digit numerator and 2-digit denominator.', 'work out squares of fractions', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of squares of fractions by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve square exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we find the square of a fraction by multiplying it by itself?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Fraction charts or rectangular paper cut-outs to show fractions\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of the concept\n* Written exercise with problems on squaring fractions with 1-digit numerators and 2-digit denominators', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL);
INSERT INTO `scheme_of_work` (`id`, `learning_area_id`, `week`, `lesson`, `strand`, `sub_strand`, `slo_cd`, `slo_sow`, `le_cd`, `le_sow`, `key_inquiry`, `resources`, `assessment`, `remarks`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `term`) VALUES
(536, 3, 6, 3, '1.0 Numbers', '1.4 Fractions', 'express a fraction as a percentage', 'a) Define percentage as a fraction with a denominator of 100.\nb) Convert given fractions into percentages accurately.', 'express a fraction as a percentage', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of converting fractions to percentages by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we express a fraction as a number out of 100?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* 100-square grid drawn on paper or chalkboard (10×10 grid)\n* Fraction charts or circular cut-outs divided into parts', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of percentage as a fraction with denominator 100\n* Written exercise where learners convert given fractions to percentages individually', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(537, 3, 6, 4, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'identify decimals up to ten thousandths in different situations', 'a) Identify the place value of digits in decimals up to ten thousandths.\nb) Read and write decimal numbers up to four decimal places correctly.', 'identify decimals up to ten thousandths in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of decimal place value by responding to guiding questions and completing steps on the chalkboard.\n* Perform or solve place value exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we name and describe the exact position of each digit in a decimal number like 0.2345?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Place value chart drawn on chalkboard or manila paper\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of place value positions\n* Written exercise where learners identify place values and write decimal numbers up to four decimal places', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(538, 3, 6, 5, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'round off decimals up to 3 decimal places in different situations', 'a) Identify the rounding digit for the first decimal place (tenths).\nb) Round off given decimals to 1 decimal place accurately.', 'round off decimals up to 3 decimal places in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of rounding decimals by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve rounding exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we round off decimals to 1 decimal place?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(539, 3, 7, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'round off decimals up to 3 decimal places', 'a) Identify the rounding digit for the second decimal place (hundredths).\nb) Round off given decimals to 2 decimal places accurately.', 'round off decimals up to 3 decimal places', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of rounding to two decimal places by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve rounding exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we decide which digit to keep when rounding a decimal number to two decimal places?', '* Learners textbook\n* Place value charts drawn on manila paper or cardboard\n* Number cards made from cardboard showing decimals to 3 or 4 decimal places\n* Chalkboard for demonstrating rounding steps', '* Oral questions during interactive demonstration to check understanding of identifying the rounding digit\n* Written exercise where learners round given decimals to 2 decimal places individually', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(540, 3, 7, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'round off decimals up to 3 decimal places', 'a) Identify the rounding digit for the third decimal place (thousandths).\nb) Round off given decimals to 3 decimal places accurately.', 'round off decimals up to 3 decimal places', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of rounding to three decimal places by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve rounding exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we round off decimals to 3 decimal places?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(541, 3, 7, 3, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'convert decimals to fractions and fractions to decimals in different situations', 'a) Identify the relationship between decimal places and denominators (10, 100, 1000, 10000).\nb) Convert given decimals into fractions in their simplest form.', 'convert decimals to fractions and fractions to decimals in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of decimal-to-fraction conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we convert decimals into fractions in their simplest form?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(542, 3, 7, 4, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'convert decimals to fractions and fractions to decimals', 'a) Use division of the numerator by the denominator to find a decimal.\nb) Convert proper fractions into decimals accurately.', 'convert decimals to fractions and fractions to decimals', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of fraction-to-decimal conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we write a fraction as a decimal number using division?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Fraction cards made from cardboard or paper', '* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of the division process\n* Written exercise converting proper fractions to decimals in exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(543, 3, 7, 5, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'convert decimals to percentages and percentages to decimals in different situations', 'a) Multiply a decimal by 100 to determine its percentage value.\nb) Convert given decimals into percentages correctly.', 'convert decimals to percentages and percentages to decimals in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of decimal-to-percentage conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we express decimals as percentages to compare and communicate values in everyday situations?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Number cards or small pieces of paper with decimals written on them', '* Written exercise (converting decimals to percentages)\n* Oral questions (explaining the conversion process and relationship between decimals and percentages)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(544, 3, 8, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'convert decimals to percentages and percentages to decimals', 'a) Divide a percentage by 100 to determine its decimal value.\nb) Convert given percentages into decimals accurately.', 'convert decimals to percentages and percentages to decimals', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of percentage-to-decimal conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we express percentages as decimals to make calculations and comparisons easier in everyday situations?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Number cards (0-9) made from cardboard or paper\n* Place value chart drawn on manila paper or cardboard', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of the conversion process\n* Written exercise where learners individually convert given percentages to decimals in their exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(545, 3, 8, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'add decimals up to 4-decimal places in different situations', 'a) Align decimal points vertically for multi-digit addition.\nb) Add decimals up to 4-decimal places accurately.', 'add decimals up to 4-decimal places in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of decimal addition by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve addition exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we accurately add amounts of money or measurements that have different numbers of decimal places?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Place value charts (drawn or teacher-made)\n* Number cards with decimal numbers', '* Written exercise: Learners solve addition problems with decimals up to 4 decimal places\n* Observation: Teacher checks alignment of decimal points and accuracy during group work', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(546, 3, 8, 3, '1.0 Numbers', '1.5 Decimals', 'subtract decimals up to 4-decimal places in different situations', 'a) Align decimal points vertically for multi-digit subtraction.\nb) Subtract decimals up to 4-decimal places accurately.', 'subtract decimals up to 4-decimal places in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of decimal subtraction by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve subtraction exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we subtract decimal numbers accurately when they have different numbers of decimal places?', '* Learners textbook\n* Place value charts (drawn on manila paper or chalkboard)\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Number cards with decimal numbers (teacher-made from cardboard)', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of decimal alignment\n* Written exercise where learners solve decimal subtraction problems up to 4 decimal places in their exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(547, 3, 8, 4, '1.0 Numbers', '1.6 Inequalities', 'form simple inequalities in one unknown involving real-life situations', 'a) Identify the inequality symbols (>, <, >=, <=).\nb) Form simple inequalities in one unknown from given word statements.', 'form simple inequalities in one unknown involving real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of forming inequalities by responding to guiding questions and completing steps using the chalkboard or tablet.\n* Perform or solve exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use symbols to show that one quantity is greater than, less than, or equal to another?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Number cards made from cardboard (showing numbers 1-20)\n* Sticks or twigs (to form inequality symbols < and >)', '* Oral questions to identify and read inequality symbols correctly\n* Written exercise forming inequalities from word statements in exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(548, 3, 8, 5, '1.0 Numbers', '1.6 Inequalities', 'simplify inequalities in one unknown involving real-life situations', 'a) Group like terms in a simple inequality expression.\nb) Simplify inequalities in one unknown by adding or subtracting terms.', 'simplify inequalities in one unknown involving real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of simplifying inequalities by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve simplification exercises individually or in groups in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we simplify inequality expressions by grouping and combining like terms?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing inequality symbols (<, >, ≤, ≥)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during interactive demonstration to check understanding of grouping like terms\n* Written exercise where learners simplify inequalities by adding or subtracting terms', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(549, 3, 9, 1, '1.0 Numbers', '1.6 Inequalities', 'solve simple inequalities in one unknown involving real-life situations', 'a) Apply inverse operations to solve for an unknown in an inequality.\nb) Solve simple inequalities involving one step of calculation.', 'solve simple inequalities in one unknown involving real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of solving inequalities by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve solving exercises individually in exercise books following demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use inverse operations to find the unknown value that makes an inequality true?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Number line drawn on chalkboard or ground', '* Oral questions during interactive demonstration to check understanding of inverse operations\n* Written exercise solving one-step inequalities individually in exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(550, 3, 9, 2, '1.0 Numbers', '1.6 Inequalities', 'appreciate use of inequalities in real-life situations', 'a) Solve real-life problems involving inequalities (e.g., age or price limits).\nb) Evaluate proficiency in inequalities through a summary exercise.', 'appreciate use of inequalities in real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive review of inequalities by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve a summary assessment exercise individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use inequalities to solve everyday problems such as determining age restrictions or checking if we have enough money to buy items?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Sample real-life scenarios written on paper (e.g., matatu fare limits, shop price lists, school age requirements)', '* Written exercise: Learners individually solve a summary assessment exercise with real-life inequality problems in their exercise books\n* Self-assessment: Learners review their work against model answers to identify areas for improvement', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(551, 3, 9, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'use the millimetre (mm) as a unit of measuring length in different situations', 'a) Identify the millimetre (mm) marks on a ruler or tape measure.\nb) Measure the length of small objects in millimetres accurately.', 'use the millimetre (mm) as a unit of measuring length in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of measuring in mm by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve measurement exercises individually using textbooks and rulers.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we measure very small objects accurately using the smallest marks on a ruler?', '* Learners textbook\n* 30 cm rulers with millimetre markings\n* Small objects to measure (seeds, small leaves, thorns, needles, small sticks, pencil lead thickness)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Observation during practical measuring activities to check correct identification of mm marks and accuracy\n* Written exercise measuring given small objects and recording lengths in millimetres', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(552, 3, 9, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'establish the relationship between the millimetre and centimetre', 'a) State the number of millimetres in one centimetre (1 cm = 10 mm).\nb) Compare lengths given in mm and cm.', 'establish the relationship between the millimetre and centimetre', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of the relationship between mm and cm by responding to guiding questions.\n* Perform or solve comparison exercises in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we measure and compare very small lengths accurately using millimetres and centimetres?', '* Learners textbook\n* Rulers marked with both centimetres and millimetres\n* Small classroom objects (pencils, erasers, chalk pieces, sticks, seeds)\n* Chalkboard and chalk for demonstrations', '* Oral questions to test understanding of the relationship between mm and cm\n* Written exercise comparing lengths given in mm and cm', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(553, 3, 9, 5, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'convert centimetres and millimetres to millimetres', 'a) Convert measurements from centimetres into millimetres.\nb) Convert measurements from millimetres into centimetres.', 'convert centimetres and millimetres to millimetres', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of length conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we change length measurements from centimetres to millimetres and from millimetres to centimetres?', '* Learners textbook\n* Metre rule with both centimetre and millimetre markings\n* Exercise books\n* Chalkboard and chalk', '* Written exercise on conversion problems in exercise books\n* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(554, 3, 10, 1, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'add centimetres and millimetres in different situations', 'a) Align measurements in cm and mm for addition.\nb) Add lengths involving centimetres and millimetres accurately.', 'add centimetres and millimetres in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of adding lengths by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve addition exercises in groups or individually.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we accurately combine measurements that have both centimetres and millimetres?', '* Learners textbook\n* Rulers marked in centimetres and millimetres\n* Sticks or twigs of different lengths\n* Strips of paper or cardboard cut to various lengths', '* Written exercise (solving addition problems with cm and mm)\n* Observation (checking alignment and accuracy during group work)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(555, 3, 10, 2, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'subtract centimetres and millimetres in different situations', 'a) Align measurements in cm and mm for subtraction.\nb) Subtract lengths involving centimetres and millimetres including regrouping.', 'subtract centimetres and millimetres in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of subtracting lengths by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve subtraction exercises individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we subtract lengths accurately when we need to regroup millimetres and centimetres?', '* Learners textbook\n* Rulers marked in centimetres and millimetres\n* Sticks or twigs of different lengths\n* Chalkboard and chalk for demonstration', '* Written exercise on subtracting lengths with regrouping in exercise books\n* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of alignment and regrouping', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(556, 3, 10, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'multiply centimetres and millimetres by whole numbers', 'a) Multiply lengths in cm and mm by a single-digit whole number.\nb) Express the product in both cm and mm where necessary.', 'multiply centimetres and millimetres by whole numbers', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of multiplying lengths by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve multiplication exercises individually or in groups.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find the total length when we multiply a measurement in centimetres and millimetres by a whole number?', '* Learners textbook\n* Rulers marked in cm and mm\n* Sticks or twigs cut to specific lengths (e.g. 12 cm 5 mm)\n* Chalkboard and chalk for demonstration', '* Written exercise solving multiplication of lengths problems\n* Oral questions to explain conversion between cm and mm in products', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(557, 3, 10, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'divide centimetres and millimetres by whole numbers', 'a) Divide lengths in cm and mm by a single-digit whole number.\nb) Apply division of length to solve real-life sharing problems.', 'divide centimetres and millimetres by whole numbers', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of dividing length by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve division exercises in exercise books following demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we share or divide a given length equally among a number of people or parts?', '* Learners textbook\n* Metre rule or tape measure\n* Ribbons, strings, or sticks of known lengths (measured in cm and mm)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to assess understanding of division of length\n* Written exercise involving division of lengths in cm and mm by single-digit numbers and solving real-life sharing problems', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(558, 3, 10, 5, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'identify the relationship between circumference and diameter', 'a) Identify the circumference, diameter, and radius of a circle.\nb) Describe the relationship between the circumference and diameter of a circle.', 'identify the relationship between circumference and diameter', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of circle parts by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve identification exercises individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find and describe the different parts of a circle and discover the relationship between the distance around it and the distance across it?', '* Learners textbook\n* Circular objects from the environment (plates, lids, buckets, bicycle wheels, coins)\n* Strings or flexible wires for measuring around circles\n* Metre rule or ruler\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions to identify circumference, diameter, and radius on different circular objects\n* Written exercise where learners measure and calculate to describe the relationship between circumference and diameter\n* Observation during practical measurement activities using circular objects and string', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(559, 3, 11, 1, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'identify the relationship between circumference and diameter in different situations', 'a) Define the terms diameter and radius.\nb) Calculate the diameter of a circle given the radius and vice versa.', 'identify the relationship between circumference and diameter in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of circle properties by responding to guiding questions and completing steps on the chalkboard.\n* Perform or solve diameter and radius exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we describe and measure the parts that run across and from the center of a circle?', '* Learners textbook\n* Circular objects (lids, plates, bicycle wheels, coins)\n* Metre rule or ruler\n* String or thread\n* Chalk and chalkboard', '* Oral questions on the definitions of diameter and radius\n* Written exercise calculating diameter from radius and vice versa', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(560, 3, 11, 2, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'identify the relationship between circumference and diameter', 'a) Measure the circumference and diameter of various circular objects using a string or tape.\nb) Discover the constant relationship (pi) between circumference and diameter.', 'identify the relationship between circumference and diameter', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of measuring circles by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve relationship discovery exercises in groups using available circular objects.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find out if there is a special relationship between the distance around a circle and the distance across it?', '* Learners textbook\n* String or sisal twine\n* Tape measure or metre rule\n* Circular objects (plates, lids, tins, bicycle wheels, buckets)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Observation during group practical measuring activities\n* Written exercise calculating and comparing circumference-to-diameter ratios\n* Oral questions about the relationship discovered between circumference and diameter', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(561, 3, 11, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'appreciate use of length in real-life situations', 'a) Solve word problems involving the conversion of mm, cm, and m.\nb) Apply measurement skills to estimate lengths of school structures.', 'appreciate use of length in real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of real-life length applications by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve word problems individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use our knowledge of converting millimetres, centimetres, and metres to solve everyday problems in our school and community?', '* Learners textbook\n* Metre rule or tape measure\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* School structures (classroom walls, doors, windows, desks)', '* Written exercise: Learners solve word problems involving conversion of mm, cm, and m in their exercise books\n* Observation: Teacher observes learners as they estimate and measure lengths of school structures during practical activity', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(562, 3, 11, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.1 Length', 'appreciate use of length', 'a) Evaluate mastery of conversion, addition, and subtraction of length units.\nb) Review common errors in measuring small objects.', 'appreciate use of length', '* Engage in an interactive review of length concepts by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve a summary assessment exercise individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we check our accuracy and avoid common mistakes when measuring and calculating with different units of length?', '* Learners textbook\n* Metre rule or tape measure\n* Small objects from the classroom (pencils, erasers, small sticks)\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books', '* Written exercise (summary assessment completed individually in exercise books)\n* Oral questions (during interactive review to gauge understanding of conversion and common errors)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(563, 3, 11, 5, '2.0 Measurement', '2.2 Area', 'work out area of triangles in square centimetres (cm2)', 'a) Identify the base and the height of a right-angled triangle.\nb) Calculate the area of a triangle using the formula A = 1/2 x base x height.', 'work out area of triangles in square centimetres (cm2)', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of the area formula by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve area exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find the area of a right-angled triangle using what we know about rectangles?', '* Learners textbook\n* Rectangular paper cut-outs (from old newspapers or exercise book pages)\n* Scissors\n* Rulers\n* Chalkboard and chalk', '* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of base, height and formula\n* Written exercise with problems calculating area of triangles using A = 1/2 × base × height', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(564, 3, 12, 1, '2.0 Measurement', '2.2 Area', 'work out area of combined shapes involving squares', 'a) Break down a combined shape into simple squares and rectangles.\nb) Calculate the total area of combined shapes accurately.', 'work out area of combined shapes involving squares', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of dissecting shapes by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve combined area exercises in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find the total area of a shape made up of rectangles and squares?', '* Learners textbook\n* Cardboard or manila paper cut into rectangles and squares of different sizes\n* Rulers\n* Chalkboard grid drawn with 1 cm squares\n* Exercise books', '* Observation during group work as learners break down combined shapes and calculate areas\n* Written exercise with problems requiring learners to find areas of combined shapes', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(565, 3, 12, 2, '2.0 Measurement', '2.2 Area', 'estimate the area of circles by counting squares', 'a) Place circular objects on a square-grid paper.\nb) Estimate the area of the circle by counting full and half-squares.', 'estimate the area of circles by counting squares', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of area estimation by responding to guiding questions and completing steps using the chalkboard grid.\n* Perform or solve estimation exercises individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we find the area of a circular object when it does not fit perfectly into squares?', '* Learners textbook\n* Square-grid paper (1 cm grid drawn on plain paper or chalkboard)\n* Circular objects of different sizes (bottle tops, lids, coins, bangles)\n* Rulers', '* Observation during the practical activity of placing circular objects on grid paper and counting squares\n* Written exercise where learners estimate the area of given circles by counting full and half-squares in their exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(566, 3, 12, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.3 Capacity', 'identify relationship among cubic centimetres (cm3), millilitres and litres', 'a) Define the unit cubic centimetre (cm3).\nb) Establish the relationship between cm3, millilitres, and litres.', 'identify relationship among cubic centimetres (cm3), millilitres and litres', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of capacity units by responding to guiding questions and completing steps on the chalkboard.\n* Perform or solve unit relationship exercises in exercise books individually using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use cubic centimetres to measure and compare the capacity of different containers?', '* Learners textbook\n* Small cubic containers (1 cm³ boxes made from cardboard or matchboxes)\n* Transparent containers of different sizes (bottles, cups, jars)\n* Water or sand for filling\n* Graduated cylinders or measuring cups marked in millilitres', '* Oral questions to check understanding of the relationship between cm³, millilitres, and litres\n* Written exercise converting between cm³, millilitres, and litres in exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(567, 3, 12, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.3 Capacity', 'identify relationship among cm3, ml and litres', 'a) Use the relationship 1 litre = 1000 cm3 in calculations.\nb) Calculate capacity in litres given values in cubic centimetres.', 'identify relationship among cm3, ml and litres', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of unit conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve capacity exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we convert measurements between cubic centimetres and litres to solve real-life capacity problems?', '* Learners textbook\n* Containers of different sizes (bottles, cups, jerry cans)\n* Water or sand for measuring\n* Rulers or measuring tapes', '* Written exercise on converting between cm³ and litres\n* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of the conversion relationship', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(568, 3, 12, 5, '2.0 Measurement', '2.3 Capacity', 'convert litres to millilitres in different situations', 'a) Identify the conversion factor between litres and millilitres.\nb) Convert given capacity from litres into millilitres accurately.', 'convert litres to millilitres in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of converting litres to millilitres by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How many millilitres make one litre and how can we use this to convert between the two units?', '* Learners textbook\n* Empty 1-litre water bottles or containers with litre markings\n* Empty smaller containers (cups, bottles) with millilitre markings or labels\n* Water for demonstration purposes\n* Chalkboard and chalk for showing conversion steps', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of the conversion factor\n* Written exercise where learners individually convert given capacities from litres to millilitres in their exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(569, 3, 13, 1, '2.0 Measurement', '2.3 Capacity', 'convert millilitres to litres in different situations', 'a) Identify the division factor needed to change millilitres to litres.\nb) Convert given capacity from millilitres into litres accurately.', 'convert millilitres to litres in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of converting ml to litres by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How many millilitres make one litre and how can we use this to convert between the two units?', '* Learners textbook\n* Empty 1-litre water bottles or soda bottles with labels\n* Smaller containers marked in millilitres (250ml cups, 500ml bottles)\n* Water for demonstration\n* Chart showing conversion factor (1000ml = 1L)', '* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of the division factor\n* Written exercise converting given capacities from millilitres to litres', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(570, 3, 13, 2, '2.0 Measurement', '2.3 Capacity', 'convert capacity between units', 'a) Convert cubic centimetres (cm3) to millilitres and vice versa.\nb) Solve simple capacity conversion problems involving cm3 and ml.', 'convert capacity between units', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of the 1:1 relationship between cm3 and ml by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve relationship exercises individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we show that one cubic centimetre is equal to one millilitre?', '* Learners textbook\n* Transparent containers or bottles with ml markings\n* Small cube-shaped boxes or containers measuring 1 cm × 1 cm × 1 cm\n* Water\n* Rulers', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration on the relationship between cm³ and ml\n* Written exercise solving conversion problems between cm³ and ml in exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(571, 3, 13, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.3 Capacity', 'appreciate use of cm3 and litres in real life', 'a) Solve real-life word problems involving capacity units (cm3, ml, and litres).\nb) Evaluate mastery of capacity through a summary exercise.', 'appreciate use of cm3 and litres in real life', '* Engage in an interactive review of capacity by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve a summary assessment exercise individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use our knowledge of capacity units to solve everyday problems in our homes and community?', '* Learners textbook\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Sample containers (bottles, cups, jerrycans) with capacity labels\n* Chart showing conversion between cm³, ml, and litres', '* Written exercise (individual summary assessment in exercise books)\n* Oral questions (during interactive review to check understanding of capacity problem-solving)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(572, 3, 13, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'identify the tonne as a unit for measuring mass in real life', 'a) Identify the tonne (t) as a unit for measuring very heavy mass.\nb) Name various commodities measured in tonnes in the community.', 'identify the tonne as a unit for measuring mass in real life', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of large mass units by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve identification exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'What objects or goods in our community are so heavy that we need to measure them in tonnes?', '* Learners textbook\n* Pictures or labels from sacks of farm produce (maize, tea, coffee, fertilizer)\n* Chart showing tonne symbol (t) and examples\n* Community resource persons (farmer, lorry driver, or trader)', '* Oral questions asking learners to name commodities measured in tonnes and explain why\n* Written exercise where learners identify and list items from the community measured in tonnes', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(573, 3, 13, 5, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'identify the relationship between the kilogramme and the tonne', 'a) State the relationship between the kilogramme and the tonne (1 tonne = 1000 kg).\nb) Compare masses given in kilogrammes and tonnes.', 'identify the relationship between the kilogramme and the tonne', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of the kg-to-tonne relationship by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve relationship exercises in exercise books individually.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we express and compare very large masses using kilogrammes and tonnes?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing 1 tonne = 1000 kg with examples (lorry, elephant, small car)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration on the kg-to-tonne relationship\n* Written exercise comparing and converting masses given in kilogrammes and tonnes', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(574, 3, 14, 1, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'estimate mass in tonnes in different situations', 'a) Estimate the mass of heavy items (e.g., a truckload of sand) in tonnes.\nb) Compare estimated mass with actual recorded mass of community items.', 'estimate mass in tonnes in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of mass estimation by responding to guiding questions and completing steps using real-life examples.\n* Perform or solve estimation exercises in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we estimate the mass of very heavy items like a truckload of sand or building materials in our community?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chart showing common heavy items and their approximate masses in tonnes (truck, tractor, water tank, bags of cement)\n* Exercise books and pencils for recording estimates\n* Pictures or drawings of heavy vehicles and items from the local community', '* Oral questions to assess learners\' understanding of estimation strategies and tonne as a unit\n* Written exercise where learners estimate masses of given heavy items and compare with actual recorded values\n* Observation during group estimation activities', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(575, 3, 14, 2, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'convert kilogrammes to tonnes and tonnes to kilogrammes', 'a) Use the conversion factor to change kilogrammes into tonnes.\nb) Convert given masses from kilogrammes to tonnes accurately.', 'convert kilogrammes to tonnes and tonnes to kilogrammes', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of mass conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps on the chalkboard.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we express very large masses measured in kilogrammes using tonnes to make them easier to understand and communicate?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing conversion factor (1 tonne = 1000 kg)\n* Real-life examples written on cards (e.g. mass of lorry, truck load of maize, water tank)', '* Written exercise converting kilogrammes to tonnes\n* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of conversion steps', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(576, 3, 14, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'convert tonnes to kilogrammes', 'a) Use the conversion factor to change tonnes into kilogrammes.\nb) Convert given masses from tonnes to kilogrammes accurately.', 'convert tonnes to kilogrammes', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of mass conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use the relationship between tonnes and kilogrammes to convert large masses from one unit to the other?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing conversion factor (1 tonne = 1000 kg)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Written exercise (solving conversion problems from tonnes to kilogrammes)\n* Oral questions (explaining the conversion process and factor used)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(577, 3, 14, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'add tonnes and kilogrammes in real-life situations', 'a) Align mass measurements in tonnes and kilogrammes for addition.\nb) Add masses involving tonnes and kilogrammes accurately.', 'add tonnes and kilogrammes in real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of adding mass by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve addition exercises in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we add masses that are measured in both tonnes and kilogrammes?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Chart showing conversion between tonnes and kilogrammes (1 tonne = 1000 kg)', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of alignment and addition steps\n* Written exercise with problems on adding masses in tonnes and kilogrammes\n* Observation of group work to assess ability to apply demonstrated procedures', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(578, 3, 14, 5, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'subtract tonnes and kilogrammes in real-life situations', 'a) Align mass measurements for subtraction including regrouping from tonnes to kg.\nb) Subtract masses involving tonnes and kilogrammes accurately.', 'subtract tonnes and kilogrammes in real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of subtracting mass by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve subtraction exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we subtract masses when the kilograms we have are not enough and we need to regroup from tonnes?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing tonne to kilogram conversion (1 tonne = 1000 kg)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the demonstration to check understanding of regrouping process\n* Written exercise with subtraction problems involving tonnes and kilograms with regrouping', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(579, 3, 15, 1, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'multiply tonnes and kilogrammes by whole numbers', 'a) Multiply mass in tonnes and kg by a single-digit whole number.\nb) Carry out multiplication and convert kg to tonnes where necessary.', 'multiply tonnes and kilogrammes by whole numbers', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of multiplying mass by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve multiplication exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we multiply mass measurements in tonnes and kilograms by whole numbers and convert between these units when needed?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing conversion: 1 tonne = 1000 kg\n* Stones or sacks labeled with sample masses (e.g., 2 tonnes 500 kg, 3 tonnes 250 kg)', '* Written exercise solving multiplication problems involving tonnes and kilograms with conversions\n* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of multiplication steps and conversion procedures', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(580, 3, 15, 2, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'divide tonnes and kilogrammes by whole numbers', 'a) Divide mass in tonnes and kg by a single-digit whole number.\nb) Apply division of mass to solve real-life distribution problems.', 'divide tonnes and kilogrammes by whole numbers', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of dividing mass by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve division exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we share or divide large masses measured in tonnes and kilograms fairly among groups or into equal parts?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Sample problems written on cards or paper (e.g. truck loads, harvest distribution, construction materials)', '* Written exercise with division problems involving tonnes and kilograms\n* Oral questions during demonstration to check understanding of division steps and real-life application', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL);
INSERT INTO `scheme_of_work` (`id`, `learning_area_id`, `week`, `lesson`, `strand`, `sub_strand`, `slo_cd`, `slo_sow`, `le_cd`, `le_sow`, `key_inquiry`, `resources`, `assessment`, `remarks`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `term`) VALUES
(581, 3, 15, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.4 Mass', 'appreciate use of the kilogramme and tonne', 'a) Solve word problems involving mass units (kg and tonnes).\nb) Evaluate mastery of mass through a summary assessment exercise.', 'appreciate use of the kilogramme and tonne', '* Engage in an interactive review of mass by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve a summary assessment exercise individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do we apply our knowledge of kilograms and tonnes to solve real-world problems involving mass?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Sample word problem scenarios written on cards or chart (e.g., truck loads, farm produce, construction materials)', '* Written exercise (summary assessment completed individually in exercise books)\n* Oral questions (during interactive review to gauge understanding before assessment)\n* Peer assessment (learners exchange books to mark and provide feedback)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(582, 3, 15, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.5 Time', 'identify and write time in a.m. and p.m.', 'a) Identify the meaning of a.m. and p.m. in relation to the day.\nb) Write time in a.m. and p.m. correctly from clock faces.', 'identify and write time in a.m. and p.m.', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of a.m./p.m. by responding to guiding questions and completing steps using the tablet or chalkboard.\n* Perform or solve time writing exercises individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we tell whether a time on the clock is in the morning or in the afternoon?', '* Learners textbook\n* Teacher-made cardboard clock with movable hands\n* Chalkboard chart showing 24-hour day divided into a.m. and p.m.\n* Sample daily school timetable with a.m. and p.m. times', '* Oral questions asking learners to identify whether given times are a.m. or p.m. and explain why\n* Written exercise where learners read clock faces and write times using a.m. or p.m. notation', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(583, 3, 15, 5, '2.0 Measurement', '2.5 Time', 'relate time in a.m. and p.m. to the 24h clock system', 'a) Describe the 24-hour clock system and its advantages.\nb) Relate a.m. and p.m. times to their corresponding 24-hour values.', 'relate time in a.m. and p.m. to the 24h clock system', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of the 24-hour clock by responding to guiding questions and completing steps on the chalkboard.\n* Perform or solve time relationship exercises individually in exercise books using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use the 24-hour clock system to avoid confusion between morning and afternoon times?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Teacher\'s smartphone or watch showing time\n* Sample timetables or schedules from the school', '* Oral questions during the interactive demonstration to check understanding of 24-hour clock advantages\n* Written exercise converting between 12-hour (a.m./p.m.) and 24-hour time formats', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(584, 3, 16, 1, '2.0 Measurement', '2.5 Time', 'convert time from 12h to 24h and 24h to 12h system', 'a) Convert time from the 12-hour system to the 24-hour system.\nb) Convert time from the 24-hour system to the 12-hour system accurately.', 'convert time from 12h to 24h and 24h to 12h system', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of time conversion by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve conversion exercises individually or in groups using the tablet or textbook.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we express the same moment in time using both the 12-hour and 24-hour systems?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Chart showing 12-hour and 24-hour time comparison\n* Teacher\'s smartphone/tablet showing digital time displays', '* Written exercise on converting times between 12-hour and 24-hour systems\n* Oral questions during the conversion demonstration\n* Peer assessment of group conversion exercises', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(585, 3, 16, 2, '2.0 Measurement', '2.5 Time', 'interpret travel timetable in different situations', 'a) Identify the components of a travel timetable (departure/arrival times).\nb) Interpret travel information from a given bus or train timetable.', 'interpret travel timetable in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of reading timetables by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve timetable interpretation exercises in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use a travel timetable to find out when buses or trains arrive and depart?', '* Learners textbook\n* Sample bus or matatu timetables (from local bus stations or created by teacher)\n* Train timetable samples (printed or drawn on manila paper)\n* Chalkboard and chalk for demonstration', '* Oral questions during guided practice on reading departure and arrival times\n* Written exercise interpreting timetable information in groups', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(586, 3, 16, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.5 Time', 'appreciate use of time in both 12h and 24h systems', 'a) Calculate time durations between departure and arrival using travel timetables.\nb) Evaluate mastery of time concepts through a summary exercise.', 'appreciate use of time in both 12h and 24h systems', '* Engage in an interactive review of time by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve a summary assessment exercise individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use travel timetables to calculate the time taken for journeys between different places?', '* Learners textbook\n* Sample travel timetables (bus, train, or matatu schedules from local transport)\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Written exercise (summary assessment completed individually in exercise books)\n* Oral questions (during interactive review to gauge understanding of time concepts)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(587, 3, 16, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.6 Money', 'prepare simple budget in different situations', 'a) Identify the components of a price list.\nb) Prepare a simple price list for items in the local community.', 'prepare simple budget in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of price lists by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve price list exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do businesses organize and display their prices to help customers make buying decisions?', '* Learners textbook\n* Sample price lists from local shops or markets\n* Manila paper or cardboard for creating price lists\n* Pictures or actual items from the local community (e.g., maize, beans, sugar, soap)', '* Oral questions to identify components of a price list\n* Practical work: Learners prepare a simple price list for local items\n* Peer assessment of the prepared price lists', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(588, 3, 16, 5, '2.0 Measurement', '2.6 Money', 'prepare simple budget', 'a) Define a budget and its importance in financial planning.\nb) Prepare a simple budget for a given amount of money.', 'prepare simple budget', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of budgeting by responding to guiding questions and completing steps using the tablet or chalkboard.\n* Perform or solve budgeting exercises individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can you plan to spend money wisely to meet your needs without running out?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Sample price lists from local shops or markets\n* Exercise books and pens', '* Oral questions to assess understanding of budget definition and importance\n* Written exercise evaluating accuracy and completeness of prepared budgets', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(589, 3, 17, 1, '2.0 Measurement', '2.6 Money', 'work out profit from sales', 'a) Define the terms \"buying price\" and \"selling price\".\nb) Calculate profit made from the sale of various items.', 'work out profit from sales', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of profit calculation by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve profit exercises individually or in groups using demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How do you calculate the profit a trader makes when they sell an item for more than they bought it?', '* Learners textbook\n* Sample items with clearly marked buying and selling prices (e.g. pencils, erasers, exercise books from school shop or brought from home)\n* Chart showing buying price, selling price, and profit formula\n* Real or play money (coins and notes) for demonstration', '* Oral questions during interactive demonstration to check understanding of buying price, selling price, and profit\n* Written exercise where learners calculate profit from given buying and selling prices of various items', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(590, 3, 17, 2, '2.0 Measurement', '2.6 Money', 'calculate loss realised from sales', 'a) Identify situations where a loss is incurred in a transaction.\nb) Calculate the loss realised from the sale of different items.', 'calculate loss realised from sales', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of loss calculation by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve loss exercises individually in exercise books following demonstrated procedures.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can you tell if a business has made a loss and how much money was lost?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chart showing sample buying and selling prices\n* Real items with price tags (e.g. books, pens, fruits)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during the demonstration to check understanding of loss situations\n* Written exercise where learners calculate loss from given transactions', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(591, 3, 17, 3, '2.0 Measurement', '2.6 Money', 'identify types of taxes in different situations', 'a) Identify Income Tax and Value Added Tax (VAT).\nb) Discuss the importance of paying taxes for national development.', 'identify types of taxes in different situations', '* Engage in an interactive demonstration of tax types by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve tax identification exercises individually or in groups.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'Why do we pay taxes and how do businesses collect VAT and individuals pay Income Tax?', '* Learners textbook\n* Sample receipts or price tags from local shops showing VAT\n* Manila paper and markers for tax charts\n* Teacher\'s smartphone (if available) to show digital tax examples', '* Oral questions on identification and importance of Income Tax and VAT\n* Written exercise involving tax identification scenarios and discussions on national development', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(592, 3, 17, 4, '2.0 Measurement', '2.6 Money', 'appreciate use of money in real-life situations', 'a) Solve real-life word problems involving profit, loss, and budgets.\nb) Evaluate proficiency in money concepts through a summary assessment.', 'appreciate use of money in real-life situations', '* Engage in an interactive review of money by responding to guiding questions and completing steps.\n* Perform or solve a summary assessment exercise individually in exercise books.\n* Receive assessment and feedback to improve understanding and performance.', 'How can we use profit, loss, and budgeting knowledge to solve everyday money problems in our homes and community?', '* Learners textbook\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Sample word problems written on chalkboard (market scenarios, small business, household budgets)\n* Local price examples (maize, milk, vegetables from nearby market)', '* Written exercise (summary assessment on profit, loss, and budget word problems)\n* Oral questions (during interactive review to check understanding of key concepts)\n* Self-assessment (learners reflect on their performance and identify areas for improvement)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(593, 3, 17, 5, '3.0 Geometry', '3.1 Lines', 'identify types of lines in different situations', 'a) Identify and name different types of lines (straight, curved, horizontal, vertical).\nb) Draw examples of each type of line in the environment.', 'identify types of lines in different situations', '* Identify types of lines around the school compound and in the classroom.\n* Draw examples of each type of line in exercise books and share with the class.', 'Where can we find different types of lines in our classroom and school compound?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* 30 cm rulers\n* Sticks or straight edges from the environment', '* Observation during identification of lines around the school compound\n* Written exercise drawing and labeling different types of lines in exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(594, 3, 18, 1, '3.0 Geometry', '3.1 Lines', 'identify parallel lines in different situations', 'a) Define parallel lines.\nb) Identify parallel lines in shapes and the environment.', 'identify parallel lines in different situations', '* Identify parallel lines in classroom structures and objects.\n* Draw parallel lines freehand and share examples with the class.', 'Where can we find examples of parallel lines in our classroom and everyday surroundings?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* 30 cm rulers\n* Classroom objects (desks, windows, door frames, floor tiles)', '* Oral questions to define and explain parallel lines\n* Observation during identification of parallel lines in the environment\n* Written exercise drawing and labeling parallel lines', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(595, 3, 18, 2, '3.0 Geometry', '3.1 Lines', 'identify perpendicular lines in different situations', 'a) Define perpendicular lines.\nb) Identify perpendicular lines in shapes and structures.', 'identify perpendicular lines in different situations', '* Identify perpendicular lines in corners of rooms and objects.\n* Draw perpendicular lines and verify using a set square.', 'Where do we find perpendicular lines in our everyday surroundings and how can we verify they are truly perpendicular?', '* Learners textbook\n* Set square or right-angled cardboard template\n* Ruler (30 cm)\n* Examples from classroom: corners of desks, windows, doors, blackboard edges', '* Observation during identification of perpendicular lines in classroom objects and structures\n* Written exercise: drawing perpendicular lines and verifying with set square\n* Oral questions on the definition and properties of perpendicular lines', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(596, 3, 18, 3, '3.0 Geometry', '3.1 Lines', 'draw parallel and perpendicular lines', 'a) Draw parallel lines using a ruler and set square.\nb) Draw perpendicular lines using a ruler and set square.', 'draw parallel and perpendicular lines', '* Draw parallel and perpendicular lines using a ruler and set square in exercise books.\n* Compare drawings with classmates and correct errors.', 'How can we use a set square and ruler to draw lines that never meet and lines that cross at right angles?', '* Learners textbook\n* Ruler (30 cm)\n* Set square\n* Pencils and erasers\n* Chalkboard ruler and set square for demonstration', '* Observation during drawing activities to check correct use of ruler and set square\n* Written exercise assessing accuracy of parallel and perpendicular lines drawn\n* Peer assessment as learners compare and correct each other\'s drawings', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(597, 3, 18, 4, '3.0 Geometry', '3.1 Lines', 'identify lines in 2-D shapes', 'a) Identify parallel and perpendicular lines in 2-D shapes.\nb) Count and categorise the types of lines in given shapes.', 'identify lines in 2-D shapes', '* Categorise lines in cut-out 2-D shapes as parallel or perpendicular.\n* Record findings in a table and share with the class.', 'How do we identify parallel and perpendicular lines in 2-D shapes?', '', '', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(598, 3, 18, 5, '3.0 Geometry', '3.1 Lines', 'appreciate use of lines in real-life situations', 'a) Relate types of lines to real-life structures and patterns.\nb) Evaluate mastery of lines through a summary exercise.', 'appreciate use of lines in real-life situations', '* Identify uses of parallel and perpendicular lines in everyday structures.\n* Complete a summary exercise individually and receive feedback.', 'How are parallel and perpendicular lines used in the structures and objects we see around us every day?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Rulers and straight edges\n* Examples from school environment (buildings, windows, doors, desks, fences)', '* Observation during identification of line types in real-life structures\n* Written summary exercise with feedback\n* Oral questions on practical applications of parallel and perpendicular lines', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(599, 3, 19, 1, '3.0 Geometry', '3.2 Angles', 'identify types of angles in different situations', 'a) Define an angle and identify its parts (arms and vertex).\nb) Classify angles as acute, right, obtuse, straight, or reflex.', 'identify types of angles in different situations', '* Identify different types of angles in the classroom environment.\n* Draw and label examples of each type of angle in exercise books.', 'What makes one angle different from another angle?', '* Learners textbook\n* Rulers\n* Pencils\n* Classroom objects (corners of books, desks, windows, door frames, clock hands)', '* Oral questions to define an angle and identify its parts\n* Written exercise to draw and label the five types of angles\n* Observation during identification of angles in the classroom environment', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(600, 3, 19, 2, '3.0 Geometry', '3.2 Angles', 'measure angles using a protractor', 'a) Identify the parts of a protractor.\nb) Measure given angles using a protractor accurately.', 'measure angles using a protractor', '* Practise reading the protractor scale in pairs.\n* Measure angles drawn on worksheets and record measurements in exercise books.', 'How can we accurately measure the size of any angle using a protractor?', '* Learners textbook\n* Protractors (one per learner or pair)\n* Worksheets with pre-drawn angles of different sizes\n* Rulers\n* Chalkboard angles drawn for demonstration', '* Observation during pair practice of protractor reading and placement\n* Written exercise checking accuracy of recorded angle measurements from worksheets', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(601, 3, 19, 3, '3.0 Geometry', '3.2 Angles', 'construct angles using a protractor', 'a) Draw a baseline and mark a vertex.\nb) Construct angles of given sizes using a protractor.', 'construct angles using a protractor', '* Construct angles of specified degrees in exercise books.\n* Compare constructed angles with a partner and correct errors.', 'How can you accurately construct angles of different sizes using a protractor?', '* Learners textbook\n* Protractors\n* Rulers\n* Pencils and erasers\n* Exercise books', '* Observation during angle construction to check correct use of protractor and accuracy\n* Peer assessment as learners compare and correct each other\'s constructed angles\n* Written exercise marking the accuracy of at least 3 angles of specified degrees', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(602, 3, 19, 4, '3.0 Geometry', '3.2 Angles', 'identify angles in shapes', 'a) Identify and name angles in triangles and quadrilaterals.\nb) Measure the angles of given polygons and record the results.', 'identify angles in shapes', '* Measure all interior angles of drawn triangles and quadrilaterals.\n* Record sums of angles and discuss findings in groups.', 'What is the sum of the interior angles in different triangles and quadrilaterals, and does it change with their shape or size?', '* Learners textbook\n* Protractors\n* Rulers\n* Pencils and erasers\n* Chart paper or exercise books for recording measurements', '* Observation during measuring and recording of angles\n* Written exercise showing measurements and calculated sums of interior angles\n* Peer assessment of group discussion findings', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(603, 3, 19, 5, '3.0 Geometry', '3.2 Angles', 'apply knowledge of angles in real-life situations', 'a) Identify angles in real-life structures (rooftops, doors, road intersections).\nb) Estimate and verify the size of angles in familiar objects.', 'apply knowledge of angles in real-life situations', '* Search for angles in the school environment and estimate their sizes.\n* Record and verify estimates using a protractor.', 'How can you find and measure angles in the structures and objects around your school?', '* Learners textbook\n* Protractors\n* Rulers\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* School structures (buildings, doors, windows, rooftops, fences, road junctions)', '* Observation during the angle-hunting activity in the school environment\n* Written exercise recording estimated and measured angles from real-life structures\n* Practical work demonstrating correct use of protractor to verify angle estimates', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(604, 3, 20, 1, '3.0 Geometry', '3.2 Angles', 'appreciate use of angles in real-life situations', 'a) Solve problems involving classification and measurement of angles.\nb) Evaluate mastery of angles through a summary exercise.', 'appreciate use of angles in real-life situations', '* Complete a summary exercise classifying and measuring angles.\n* Receive feedback and correct any misconceptions.', 'How can I accurately identify, classify, and measure different types of angles to solve real-world problems?', '* Learners textbook\n* Protractors\n* Rulers\n* Geometric sets\n* Teacher-prepared summary exercise worksheets', '* Written exercise (summary exercise covering classification and measurement of angles)\n* Peer assessment (learners exchange work to check angle classifications and measurements)\n* Self-assessment (learners reflect on their mastery and identify areas needing improvement)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(605, 3, 20, 2, '3.0 Geometry', '3.3 3-D Objects', 'identify 3-D objects in different situations', 'a) Identify and name common 3-D objects (cube, cuboid, cylinder, sphere, cone, pyramid).\nb) Relate 3-D objects to real-life examples.', 'identify 3-D objects in different situations', '* Collect 3-D objects from the environment and name them.\n* Match objects to their geometric names and share with the class.', 'What objects around us have shapes like cubes, cuboids, cylinders, spheres, cones, and pyramids?', '* Learners textbook\n* Collection of 3-D objects from the environment (boxes, tins, balls, bottles, funnel, stones)\n* Real-life items: matchbox, milk packet, toilet roll, orange, traditional hats, roof models\n* Chart showing names of 3-D shapes', '* Observation during collection and naming of 3-D objects\n* Oral questions asking learners to identify and give real-life examples of each 3-D object\n* Practical activity where learners match collected objects to geometric names', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(606, 3, 20, 3, '3.0 Geometry', '3.3 3-D Objects', 'describe properties of 3-D objects', 'a) Count and record the number of faces, edges, and vertices of given 3-D objects.\nb) Compare properties of different 3-D objects.', 'describe properties of 3-D objects', '* Handle 3-D objects and count faces, edges, and vertices.\n* Record findings in a table and compare with other groups.', 'How can we identify and compare the faces, edges, and vertices of different 3-D objects we use every day?', '* Learners textbook\n* Empty boxes (matchboxes, chalk boxes, soap boxes)\n* Tin cans and cylindrical containers\n* Stone or clay pyramids (locally made)\n* Balls or spheres (fruit, stones)', '* Observation during handling and counting of 3-D objects\n* Written exercise: Learners complete a table recording faces, edges, and vertices\n* Peer assessment of group comparison findings', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(607, 3, 20, 4, '3.0 Geometry', '3.3 3-D Objects', 'classify 3-D objects', 'a) Group 3-D objects by shared properties (flat or curved faces).\nb) Justify the classification of each object.', 'classify 3-D objects', '* Sort a collection of 3-D objects by their properties.\n* Present and justify classifications to the class.', 'What properties can we use to group different 3-D objects into families?', '* Learners textbook\n* Collection of 3-D objects from the environment (boxes, tins, balls, bottles, cones made from paper)\n* Chart paper or large sheets for grouping objects\n* Locally made models of cubes, cuboids, cylinders, pyramids, and spheres using cardboard or clay', '* Observation during sorting activity using a checklist (Can identify flat/curved faces, groups objects correctly, justifies classification)\n* Oral questions asking learners to justify why they placed specific objects in each group', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(608, 3, 20, 5, '3.0 Geometry', '3.3 3-D Objects', 'draw nets of 3-D objects', 'a) Identify the net of a cube and a cuboid.\nb) Cut out and fold nets to form 3-D objects.', 'draw nets of 3-D objects', '* Draw, cut, and fold nets to make cubes and cuboids.\n* Verify that the folded net forms the correct 3-D shape.', 'How can we open up a cube or cuboid box to see all its faces at once?', '* Learners textbook\n* Cardboard or manila paper for drawing and cutting nets\n* Scissors and rulers\n* Empty cartons or boxes (matchboxes, soap boxes, tea packets)\n* Pencils and erasers', '* Observation during the practical activity of drawing, cutting and folding nets\n* Practical work: Learners produce correctly folded cubes and cuboids from their nets\n* Peer assessment: Learners verify each other\'s folded nets to confirm they form the correct 3-D shape', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(609, 3, 21, 1, '3.0 Geometry', '3.3 3-D Objects', 'relate 3-D objects to real-life items', 'a) Name everyday items that correspond to specific 3-D shapes.\nb) Sketch the 3-D shape for a given real-life object.', 'relate 3-D objects to real-life items', '* Match photographs of real objects to their 3-D geometric forms.\n* Sketch and label the geometric shapes found in everyday items.', 'What 3-D shapes can we identify in the objects we use every day at home and in school?', '* Learners textbook\n* Collection of everyday objects (boxes, balls, tins, bottles, cups, cones from packaging)\n* Pictures or photographs of common items (buildings, water tanks, balls, dice, tents)\n* Chalkboard and chalk for demonstration sketching', '* Observation during matching activity of real objects to their 3-D shapes\n* Written exercise where learners sketch and label 3-D shapes of given everyday items', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(610, 3, 21, 2, '3.0 Geometry', '3.3 3-D Objects', 'appreciate use of 3-D objects in real-life situations', 'a) Solve problems involving properties and nets of 3-D objects.\nb) Evaluate mastery of 3-D objects through a summary exercise.', 'appreciate use of 3-D objects in real-life situations', '* Complete a summary exercise on 3-D object properties and nets.\n* Receive feedback and review common errors.', 'How can we use our understanding of 3-D object properties and nets to solve real-world problems involving containers?', '* Learners textbook\n* Sample nets of cuboids, cubes, and cylinders (from previous lessons or drawn on manila paper)\n* Actual 3-D objects (boxes, tins, cylindrical containers from the community)\n* Chalkboard and chalk for reviewing common errors', '* Written exercise (summary test on properties and nets of 3-D objects)\n* Self-assessment (learners review their answers against model solutions and identify areas of difficulty)\n* Oral questions (during feedback to clarify common errors and misconceptions)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(611, 3, 21, 3, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'collect and record data using tally marks', 'a) Define data and give examples of data collected in daily life.\nb) Use tally marks to record data from a survey.', 'collect and record data using tally marks', '* Conduct a simple class survey and record responses using tally marks.\n* Share tally results with the class and discuss.', 'How can we collect and record information about our classmates using tally marks?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Chart paper or large piece of paper (for class tally display)', '* Observation during the survey activity\n* Written exercise: learners record survey data using tally marks in exercise books\n* Oral questions on the meaning of data and examples from daily life', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(612, 3, 21, 4, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'organise data in a frequency table', 'a) Transfer tally marks into a frequency table.\nb) Identify the highest and lowest frequencies in the table.', 'organise data in a frequency table', '* Convert tally data from Lesson 1 into a frequency table.\n* Identify and discuss the highest and lowest values.', 'How do we change tally marks into numbers and find which item appears most and least often?', '* Learners textbook\n* Tally data collected in Lesson 1\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Ruler for drawing frequency table', '* Written exercise: Learners convert given tally marks into a frequency table and identify highest and lowest frequencies\n* Oral questions: Ask learners to explain which item has the most or least frequency and how they determined this', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(613, 3, 21, 5, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'identify the components of a bar graph', 'a) Identify the title, axes, labels, and scale of a bar graph.\nb) Describe the purpose of each component of a bar graph.', 'identify the components of a bar graph', '* Label the parts of a given bar graph using provided terms.\n* Discuss why each component is important for reading the graph.', 'Why does a bar graph need a title, axes, labels, and scale to be useful?', '* Learners textbook\n* Sample bar graphs from newspapers or health posters\n* Manila paper or chalkboard for drawing a large bar graph\n* Ruler for drawing straight lines and axes', '* Oral questions asking learners to explain the purpose of each component of a bar graph\n* Written exercise where learners label the parts of a given bar graph and write the function of each component', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(614, 3, 22, 1, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'draw a vertical bar graph from collected data', 'a) Choose an appropriate scale for a vertical bar graph.\nb) Draw and label a vertical bar graph from a frequency table.', 'draw a vertical bar graph from collected data', '* Draw a vertical bar graph from the class survey frequency table.\n* Ensure title, labels, and scale are included.', 'How do we choose the right scale to clearly show our survey data on a vertical bar graph?', '* Learners textbook\n* Manila paper or newsprint for drawing large bar graphs\n* Rulers (at least one per group)\n* Frequency table from class survey (prepared in previous lesson)\n* Chalkboard and chalk for demonstration', '* Observation during the drawing activity using a checklist (correct scale, accurate bars, title, labels)\n* Written exercise: learners draw and label a vertical bar graph from a given frequency table in their exercise books', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(615, 3, 22, 2, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'draw a horizontal bar graph from collected data', 'a) Choose an appropriate scale for a horizontal bar graph.\nb) Draw and label a horizontal bar graph from a frequency table.', 'draw a horizontal bar graph from collected data', '* Draw a horizontal bar graph from a provided frequency table.\n* Compare the horizontal and vertical formats and discuss.', 'How do you choose the right scale to accurately represent data on a horizontal bar graph?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Ruler\n* Sample frequency tables (from local contexts like crop harvest, school attendance, favorite sports)\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Written exercise: Learners draw and label a horizontal bar graph from a given frequency table using an appropriate scale\n* Observation: Assess learners\' ability to choose suitable scales and accurately plot bars during the drawing activity', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(616, 3, 22, 3, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'read and interpret a bar graph', 'a) Read values from bars on a given bar graph.\nb) Answer questions based on information shown in a bar graph.', 'read and interpret a bar graph', '* Read and answer questions from a given bar graph in exercise books.\n* Discuss answers as a class and correct errors.', 'How do we read and interpret information presented in a bar graph to answer questions?', '* Learners textbook\n* Bar graph charts drawn on manila paper or chalkboard showing real-life data (school enrollment, crop harvests, weekly market prices)\n* Printed or teacher-drawn bar graph worksheets\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during class discussion to check understanding of reading bar graph values\n* Written exercise marking learners\' answers to questions based on the bar graph', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(617, 3, 22, 4, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'compare information using bar graphs', 'a) Compare two sets of data displayed on the same bar graph.\nb) Draw conclusions from comparisons made on the bar graph.', 'compare information using bar graphs', '* Compare two bar graphs showing similar categories and discuss differences.\n* Write two conclusions from the comparison in exercise books.', 'What can we learn by comparing two sets of data shown on the same bar graph?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chart paper or manila paper with pre-drawn bar graphs showing two data sets\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils', '* Oral questions during group discussion of the bar graph comparisons\n* Written exercise marking the two conclusions drawn from the bar graph comparison\n* Observation of learners\' ability to identify differences between the two data sets', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(618, 3, 22, 5, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'answer questions from a bar graph', 'a) Identify the category with the highest and lowest values.\nb) Calculate the difference between values shown in a bar graph.', 'answer questions from a bar graph', '* Answer a set of comprehension questions from a bar graph individually.\n* Check answers in pairs and discuss any discrepancies.', 'How can you compare different categories in a bar graph to find the highest, lowest, and the difference between values?', '* Learners textbook\n* Sample bar graphs drawn on charts or chalkboard showing different real-life data (e.g. crop harvest, school attendance, market prices)\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Ruler for reading bar graph values accurately', '* Written exercise (learners answer comprehension questions from the bar graph individually)\n* Peer assessment (learners check answers in pairs and discuss discrepancies)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(619, 3, 23, 1, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'draw bar graphs from word problems', 'a) Extract data from a word problem to create a frequency table.\nb) Draw a bar graph from the extracted data.', 'draw bar graphs from word problems', '* Extract data from a provided word problem and draw the bar graph.\n* Compare bar graphs drawn by different groups and discuss.', 'How can we extract and organise information from a real-life story to display it visually using a bar graph?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chart paper or manila paper for drawing bar graphs\n* Rulers for drawing straight lines and axes\n* Sample word problems written on the chalkboard', '* Written exercise: Learners extract data from a word problem, create a frequency table, and draw a bar graph\n* Peer assessment: Learners compare and evaluate bar graphs drawn by different groups using given criteria', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(620, 3, 23, 2, '4.0 Data Handling', '4.1 Bar Graphs', 'appreciate use of bar graphs in real-life situations', 'a) Solve real-life problems by drawing and reading bar graphs.\nb) Evaluate mastery of bar graphs through a summary exercise.', 'appreciate use of bar graphs in real-life situations', '* Complete a summary task: draw, label, and answer questions from a bar graph.\n* Receive feedback and review errors.', 'How can you use a bar graph to solve a problem you might face in your school or community?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pencils\n* Rulers\n* Sample data sets (class attendance, crops harvested, school items sold)', '* Written exercise (summary task with drawing, labeling, and answering questions)\n* Rubrics (to evaluate accuracy of graph construction, labeling, and interpretation of data)', '', '2026-04-10 17:33:40', '2026-04-11 10:17:43', NULL),
(621, 1, 1, 1, '1.0 Foundations of Pre-Technical Studies', '1.1 Safety on Raised Platforms', 'a) identify types of raised platforms used in performing tasks', 'a) Define the term \"raised platforms.\"\nb) Identify various types of raised platforms used in performing tasks.\nc) Describe the characteristics of different raised platforms.', '• walk around the school to explore types of raised platforms (ladders, trestles, steps, stands, mobile raised platforms, work benches, ramps).\n• brainstorm on the types of raised platforms used in day-to-day life.', '• Define what is raised platforms thro question and answer.\n• Explore types of raised platforms, in groups, note down findings and share with the class.\n• Brainstorm on the types of raised platforms used in day-to-day life, in groups, and share findings with the rest of the class.', 'What are raised platforms and why are they used in different tasks at home, school, and in our community?', '* Learners textbook\n* Photographs or drawings of ladders, scaffolds, stools, and stages\n* Actual examples: classroom desk, chair, or stool\n* Chart paper and markers for group presentations', '* Oral questions during class discussions on definition and types of raised platforms\n* Observation of group work participation and accuracy of identified raised platforms\n* Written exercise: learners list and describe characteristics of at least three raised platforms', '', '2026-04-11 10:00:35', '2026-04-11 13:23:56', 1),
(622, 1, 1, 2, '1.0 Foundations of Pre-Technical Studies', '1.1 Safety on Raised Platforms', 'b) describe risks associated with working on raised platforms', 'a) Identify potential risks associated with working on raised platforms.\nb) Describe specific hazards encountered when working at different heights.', '• use print or digital media to search for information on risks associated with working on raised platforms.', '• Search for information on risk associated with working on raised platforms, in groups.  Write down findings and share them in class.', 'What dangers can workers face when performing tasks on raised platforms such as ladders, scaffolds, or rooftops?', '* Learners textbook\n* Smartphones or tablets for group research (teacher\'s or shared)\n* Charts or manila paper for recording findings\n* Pictures or drawings of raised platforms (ladders, scaffolds, buildings under construction)', '* Oral questions during group presentations to assess understanding of risks and hazards\n* Written exercise where learners list and describe at least five specific hazards associated with working at heights', '', '2026-04-11 10:00:35', '2026-04-11 13:23:56', 1),
(623, 1, 1, 3, '1.0 Foundations of Pre-Technical Studies', '1.1 Safety on Raised Platforms', 'c) observe safety when working on raised platforms', 'a) Discuss effective methods of minimizing risks when working on raised platforms.\nb) Propose safety measures for preventing falls and injuries.', '• discuss ways of minimising risks related to working on raised platforms.', '• Discuss in groups, ways of minimising risks when working on raised platforms.', 'What safety measures should be put in place to minimize risks and prevent falls when working on raised platforms?', '* Learners textbook\n* Pictures or drawings of raised platforms (scaffolding, ladders, roofs)\n* Chart paper and markers for group presentations\n* Smartphone/tablet for showing safety scenarios or videos (optional)', '* Oral questions during and after group discussions\n* Observation of group participation and quality of proposed safety measures\n* Written exercise listing at least five safety measures for working on raised platforms', '', '2026-04-11 10:00:35', '2026-04-11 13:23:56', 1),
(624, 1, 1, 4, '1.0 Foundations of Pre-Technical Studies', '1.1 Safety on Raised Platforms', 'c) observe safety when working on raised platforms', 'a) Demonstrate safe practices for using raised platforms through role play.\nb) Critique safety behaviors observed during the role play session.', '• role-play safety practices for working on raised platforms.', '• Role play safety practices for working on raised platforms and share what they have learnt from each other in class.', 'How can we work safely on raised platforms to prevent accidents and injuries?', '* Learners textbook\n* Stable desks, benches, or tables (to simulate raised platforms)\n* Manila paper or chalkboard for listing safety rules\n* Teacher\'s smartphone/tablet (for showing safety images if available)', '* Observation checklist during role play (correct safety practices demonstrated)\n* Peer assessment of safety behaviors observed\n* Oral questions on safety measures for raised platforms', '', '2026-04-11 10:00:35', '2026-04-11 13:23:56', 1),
(625, NULL, 1, 1, '1.0 Foundations of Pre -Technical Studies', '1.1 Introduction to Pre-Technical Studies', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na)   identify the components of Pre-Technical Studies as a learning area,\nb)   explain the role of Pre-Technical Studies in day-to-day life,\nc)   embrace Pre-Technical Studies in career development.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•   brainstorm on the components of Pre-Technical Studies as a learning area,\n•   discuss and present the role of Pre-Technical Studies in day-to-day life,\n•   debate on the role of Pre-Technical Studies in day-to-day life.', '', 'What are some everyday problems in our community that Pre-Technical Studies could help us solve?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Exercise books and pens/pencils\n* Locally available materials (e.g., sticks, stones, containers) for demonstration\n* Teacher\'s smartphone/tablet (optional, for showing images if available)', '* Oral questions during brainstorming and discussion\n* Observation checklist for participation and teamwork during group presentations', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:51:33', NULL),
(626, NULL, 1, 2, '1.0 Foundations of Pre-Technical Studies', '1.2 Safety in the Immediate Environment', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na)   identify potential safety threats in the immediate environment,\nb)   outline safety rules and regulations for a given situation,\nc)   observe safety in the immediate environment,\nd)   appreciate the importance of observing safety in the immediate environment.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•   brainstorm with peers on potential safety threats in the immediate environment', '', '', '•   Workshop attires such as; overcoats, aprons,\nshoes, and goggles, among others.\n•   Career brochures, career magazmes\n•   Digital devices such as; computers, laptops,\nsmartphones, and tablets, among others', '•   Question and Answer\n•   Observation\n•   Written Test\n•   Practical Work\n•   Peer and Self-Assessment', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(627, NULL, 1, 3, '1.0 Foundations of Pre-Technical Studies', '1.3 Computer Concepts (6 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand the learner should be able to:\na)   explain the characteristics of a computer in a user environment,\nb)   classify computers used in day-to-day life,\nc)   use a computer to perform tasks in a user environment,\nd)   acknowledge the importance of different types of computers used in day-to-day life.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•  brainstorm on the meaning of the terms; computer, data, and information,\n•  discuss characteristics of a computer (speed, accuracy, versatility, reliability, diligence, storage, consistency),\n•  download and watch a video clip on classification of computers,\n•  discuss the classification of computers (functionality, purpose, and size) in a user environment,\n•  interact with different types of computers in the user environment to perfonn tasks.', '', 'What are the main differences between a desktop computer and a smartphone, and why might someone choose one over the other?', '* Learners textbook\n* Chalkboard and chalk\n* Pictures/diagrams of different computer types (from textbook or teacher\'s smartphone)\n* Real-life examples (e.g., a basic calculator, teacher\'s smartphone for demonstration if available)\n* Student exercise books and pens', '* Oral questions on computer classification and uses\n * Written exercise: Listing and describing types of computers used in their community', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:51:39', NULL),
(628, NULL, 1, 4, '2.0 Communication in Pre-Technical Studies', '2.1 Introduction to Drawing (10 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na)   explain the importance of drawing as a means of communication,\nb)   distinguish between artistic and technical drawings used in technical fields\nc)   print numbers and letters of the alphabet as used in drawing,\nd)   draw types of lines used in drawing,\ne)   illustrate symbols and abbreviations used in drawing,\nf)   appreciate the role of drawing in communication.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•   discuss the importance of drawing as a means of communication,\n•  brainstorm on the meaning of the terms \'technical drawing\' and \'artistic drawing,\n•   use print or online resources to search for information on artistic and technical drawing,\n•   practice printing numbers and letters of the alphabet,\n•  use visual aids to search for information on the types of lines and their application in drawing (thick and thin continuous, dashed, and chain).\n•   draw various types of lines (thick and thin continuous, dashed and chain)\n•   sketch basic symbols (0,   t, R, .l, □) and abbreviations (DRG, AIF, AIC, I/D, O/D) used in drawing\n•   use audio-visual aids to study the application of symbols and abbreviations in drawing.', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(629, NULL, 2, 1, '2.0 Communication in Pre-Technical Studies', '2.2 Free-hand sketching (IO lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na)   Explain the principles of free-hand sketching\nb)   Identify techniques of free-hand sketching\nc)   sketch lines using free-hand,\nd)   sketch 2D shapes using free hand,\ne)   appreciate the importance of free-hand sketching in communication.', '', 'Learner is guided to:\n•   discuss the meaning of free-hand sketching as used in Pre-Technical Studies,\n•   use print and digital media to search for information on freehand sketching techniques (box method, centerline method, hand compass method),(hatching, cross-hatching, stippling, and blending)\n•   use pencils and drawing papers to sketch lines,\n•   use pencils and drawing papers to sketch two-dimensional shapes,\n•   use digital media, to observe how free-hand sketches express artistic ideas in different career fields,', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL);
INSERT INTO `scheme_of_work` (`id`, `learning_area_id`, `week`, `lesson`, `strand`, `sub_strand`, `slo_cd`, `slo_sow`, `le_cd`, `le_sow`, `key_inquiry`, `resources`, `assessment`, `remarks`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `term`) VALUES
(630, NULL, 2, 2, '2.0 Communication in Pre-Technical Studies', '2.3 ICT Tools in Communication (6 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na) explain the importance of ICT tools in communication,\nb) describe the ICT tools used in communication,\nc) use ICT tools to enhance communication,\nd) acknowledge the role of communication in Pre-Technical Studies.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•  brainstorm and present on the meaning and importance of ICT tools in communication,\n•  use print or digital media to search for information on ICT tools used in communication (email, mobile phone, computers, video and web conferencing tools, social networking, and online collaboration) and present the findings,\n•  communicate using ICT tools (send and receive; email, texts, calls, chats, audio, animations and video).', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(631, NULL, 2, 3, '3.0 Materials for Production', '3.1 Introduction to Materials (6 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be to:\na)   identify materials used in production,\nb)   distinguish between metallic and non-metallic materials found in the locality,\nc)   describe sustainable ways of using malerials in production,\nd)   appreciate the importance of materials in production.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•  discuss and present the meaning of materials used in production,\n•  use print or digital media to search for information on materials used in production and share with peers,\n•  discuss the differences between metallic and non-metallic materials,\n•  sort out materials in the locality as either metallic or non-metallic,\n•  brainstorm and present sustainable ways of using materials in production,\n•  discuss and make a presentation on the importance of materials used in production.', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(632, NULL, 2, 4, '3.0 Materials for Production', '3.2 Metallic Materials (10 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(633, NULL, 3, 1, '3.0 Materials for Production', '3.3 Non-Metallic Materials (10 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na)   identify non-metallic materials found in the locality,\nb)   categorise non-metallic materials as either synthetic or natural,\nc)   describe the physical properties of non-metallic materials found in the locality,\nd)   relate non-metallic materials to their uses in the locality,\ne)   appreciate the use of non-metallic materials in production.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•   use print or digital media to search for information on non-metallic materials,\n•   discuss the non-metallic materials (wood, stone, plastics, paper, rubber, cement, glass, ceramics),\n•   sort non-metallic materials as either synthetic or natural,\n•   perform practical activities to examine the physical properties of non-metallic materials (color, texture, hardness, fire resistance),\n•   discuss the physical properties of non-metallic materials,\n•   match non-metallic materials to their use in the locality.', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(634, NULL, 3, 2, '4.0   Tools and Production', '4.1  Measuring and Marking Out Tools (18 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na)  identify measuring and marking out tools used to perform tasks,\nb) select measuring and marking out tools for a given task,\nc)  use measuring and marking out tools to perform a given task,\nd)  care for measuring and marking out tools to minimise damage,\ne)  recognise the importance of measuring and marking out tools when performing tasks.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•  use visual aids and realia to identify measuring tools (tape measure, steel rule, callipers, weighing balance, stopwatch, ammeter, voltmeter) and marking out tools (divider, try-square, marking gauge, dot punch, scriber, pencil, marking knife),\n•  choose the appropriate measuring and marking out tools to perform a given task,\n•  use available resources to search for information on the use of measuring and marking out tools,\n•  perform specific tasks using measuring and marking out tools,\n•  practice caring for measuring and marking out tools.', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(635, NULL, 3, 3, '4.0 Tools and Production', '4.2  Computer Hardware', 'By the end of the sub strand\nthe learner should be able to:\na)   classify computer hardware devices in a user environment,\nb)   use computer hardware devices to carry out a given task,\nc)   value the importance of computer hardware devices in a user environment.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•  brainstorm and present the meaning of the term \'computer hardware,\n•  use available resources to search for information on categories of\ncomputer hardware: input devices (keying devices, pointing devices, scanning devices, voice input devices, touch screen, digitizer, digital cameras), output devices (hardcopy and softcopy), storage devices (fixed and removable devices),\n•  match available devices to their\nrespective categories,\n•  perform tasks using computer\ninput, outnut, and storage devices.', '', '', '', 'SUGGESTED ASSESSMENT RUBRIC\n\nAbility to identify measuring and marking out tools used to perform tasks.\nExceeds expectations: Identifies measuring and marking out tools used to perform tasks\nand improvises more tools.\nMeets expectations: Identifies measuring and marking out tools used to perform tasks.\nApproaches expectations: Identifies measuring and marking out tools used to perform tasks leaving out a few tools.\nBelow expectations: Identifies measuring and marking out tools used to perform tasks leaving out many tools.\n\nAbility to use measuring and marking out tools to perform a given task.\nExceeds expectations: Uses measuring and marking out tools to perform a given task with high precision and\nno errors.\nMeets expectations: Uses measuring and marking out tools to perform a given task.\nApproaches expectations: Uses measuring and marking out tools to perform a given task with a few errors.\nBelow expectations: Uses measuring and marking out tools to perform a given task with many errors.\n\nAbility to use computer hardware\ndevices to carry out a given task.\nExceeds expectations: Uses computer hardware devices to carry out a given task\nand innovates more.\nMeets expectations: Uses computer hardware devices to carry out a given task.\nApproaches expectations: Uses some of the computer hardware\ndevices to carry out a given task.\nBelow expectations: Uses only a few of the computer hardware\ndevices to carry out a given task.', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(636, NULL, 3, 4, '5.0 Entrepreneurship', '5.1 Introduction to\nEntrepreneurship\n(4 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub\nstrand, the learner should be able to:\na)  explain the importance of entrepreneurship in the community,\nb)  describe the qualities of an enlrepreneur in business,\nc)  explore sources of business ideas for a business venture,\nd)  appreciate the role of entrepreneurship in a community.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•   brainstorm and present the meaning of the terms \'entrepreneur\' and\n\'entrepreneurship,', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(637, NULL, 4, 1, '5.0 Entrepreneurship', '5.2 Production Unit (6 lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na)   explain the factors considered when locating a production unit,\nb)  analyse the factors detennining the size of a production unit,\nc)   value the importance of locating a production unit in a suitable area.', '', 'The learner is guided to:\n•   discuss the meaning of the term \'production unit\' and present it to peers,\n•   brainstorm and present the factors considered when choosing the location of a production unit,\n•   visit the local community to assess the factors that influenced the location of a particular production unit (Pasho mill, salon, barber shop, welding, cybercqfe),\n•   use print or digital media to search for information on the factors that determine its size and share with peers.', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
(638, NULL, 4, 2, '5.0 Entrepreneurship', '5.3 Financial Goals (IO lessons)', 'By the end of the sub strand, the learner should be able to:\na)  explain the importance of setting goals in financial management,', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', '2026-04-12 09:21:46', NULL),
